proof
thus (I is (associative-ideal of X) implies (for x holds (for y holds (for z holds (( ( x \ y ) \ z ) in I implies ( x \ ( y \ z ) ) in I)))))
proof
assume A1: I is (associative-ideal of X);
let x;
let y;
let z;
assume that
A2: ( ( x \ y ) \ z ) in I;
( ( x \ ( x \ y ) ) \ y ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:1;
then ( x \ ( x \ y ) ) <= y by BCIALG_1:def 11;
then ( ( x \ ( x \ y ) ) \ ( y \ z ) ) <= ( y \ ( y \ z ) ) by BCIALG_1:5;
then A3: ( ( ( x \ ( x \ y ) ) \ ( y \ z ) ) \ z ) <= ( ( y \ ( y \ z ) ) \ z ) by BCIALG_1:5;
( ( y \ ( y \ z ) ) \ z ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:1;
then ( ( ( ( x \ ( x \ y ) ) \ ( y \ z ) ) \ z ) \ ( 0. X ) ) = ( 0. X ) by A3,BCIALG_1:def 11;
